Difference Between Params and Query Parameters
Route Parameter
/user/101

Route:

<Route path="/user/:id" element={<User />} />

Access using:

const { id } = useParams();
Query Parameter
/user?id=101

Access using:

const searchParams = new URLSearchParams(window.location.search);

const id = searchParams.get("id");

We'll learn a React Router way (useSearchParams) later.

Interview Questions
What is a Route Parameter?

A dynamic value passed through the URL.

Example:

/user/101

where 101 is the route parameter.

What does :id mean?

It defines a dynamic route segment.

<Route path="/user/:id" element={<User />} />
What hook is used to access route parameters?
useParams()
What does useParams() return?

An object containing all route parameters.

Example:

const { id } = useParams();
